author: El Primo
text:
Never have I wrote down a comment on a video before I think, but seeing all of your stories, your ups and downs, along with this soothing melody... Kinda has inspired me.

I'm Spanish, 21 years old. 18th and 19th years had been the worst ones I've lived so far. After I finished bachelore, I got into a vocational training on medicine - Thing I didn't like at all, but my father really insisted on it. Of course I failed and didn't dare returning home after a wasted year. Once I did, the stress was too overwhelming and my parents still kept putting too much pressure on me that, for the first time in my life, thoughts on planning for suicide drove right into my mind. The next year was also a waste, but at my 20th year I started studying programming only having a very small base on what all of it was about. Luckily for me, I met there a friend who I could perfectly consider as my best friend right now who has helped me through this degree and finally made that year not to be a complete waste. Life's been doing better since then: I've got a new group of friends after the last one left me alone for two years and I've known nothing from them since then - Not that I ever want to. My new group is the most warming and friendly I've been, and I owe them all a lot. We can't see eachother much due to the actual covid situation, but we always hang out in discord whenever we can to play some games, do some tabletop roleplaying such as D&D, or just simply stay there and talk about life. My parents also accept me more now and we get along really well, and I'm really happy that I can make them proud of me. I wouldn't ask for anything else at all. However, this last year is being stressful as heck: in our classes, a teacher that helped us the most that was supposed to teach us for another year isn't in our actual degree, and instead we have a really demanding one who gives us lots of works to do in very few time. I have to finish about 4 different projects in under 5 days at the moment I'm writting this down, and the caffeine levels in my veins are burning hot to use the most time I can have. And here I am, writting down this long personal story of mine, gathered in this fireplace of people I don't know at all. But your stories, your worries, your ups and downs... You've all inspired me to keep going and not fall behind, not after all the efforts I've made this far. These are gonna be the roughest 5 days of this year for sure, but I can't let it all go to waste now!


So that's why I wanted to write this down, maybe to share my story along with the other hundreds of stories I've read so far, and so I can hopefully inspire some of you too. Life can have great downhills, but all you gotta do is look for the right people, the right times, and no matter how many years it takes, things can always climb up to bettter places. Wherever you are, whoever you are, I wish you the best that could happen to ya.

...oh, and I'll be sure to write down here again after these 5 days if everything goes right. Good luck ya'll! ¬°Buena suerte a todos! <3

text:
Well, it seems it is about time to update my old checkpoint with a new one.
It has been almost 4 months since my last one, but here goes nothing.
Originally I was (and still am) suffering from extreme identity issues and now know I suffer from Dissociative Derealisation Disorder. Which certainly helped me know why I feel like I live my life from someone else's POV, but honestly that isn't even it now. I struggle to maintain any semblance of a relationship with a borderline abusive family that constantly belittle and breate for doing things that they taught me to do over my near 22 year life. I am confident once the lockdowns and pandemic either ease up or end I can have a chance to get away from them, even if only temporarily. But thankfully, there is finally some news in this checkpoint. I have met the boy of my dreams. I won't get into specifics, but what started as a spur of the moment "wanna try?" sort of internet relationship has blossomed into something more and I couldn't be happier. So while this checkpoint is still mostly sad, at least there is some good in the world. I know life is tough and honestly fucking sucks ass at times. I'm just glad I was able to experience some semblance of happiness this time. Since my last checkpoint, I am also getting therapy and counselling, even if scarce and sparce, but I haven't had an attempt in months. Fuck, im crying while I write this since my life has changed this drastically in just a few months.
I apologise if you read all that, but I thank you for listening to my story. 
And to me of the future when i inevitably end up back here. It does get better. It may take some time, there may not be any sunshine around the corner. But there will ALWAYS be a light at the end of the tunnel.
Stay safe everyone, i love you x
~Rai  04/02/2021

author: K. Leandro P.
text:
So, the famous corner of internet on Youtube; it have been many times Ive encountered several borders, I used to just stayed for the music and read a bit. First time I dare to write, it might be the nostalgy of playing this level and loving all about it (including the trilogy as well), or may well be that now I'm literally to the other half of the world (18.998 km in distance with geodesy straight direction)
Ive already pass by the 27 yo, this year 28 (the famous 27s club is not my thing, I reckon), my life is not full of luxury or lack of needs; but Ive never experienced prolonged hunger, since child I was the promise of my family (supposedly more intelligent than other Childs), and whilst growing, a model for others regarding my academic consistency and willingness (for many things). I was awardee in my undergraduate, now Im also have a full  post-graduate scholarship in this new country, before Ive never suffered unemployment, just before leaving my country I had to reject various offerings (following my "dreams"). Ive never had to look for much attention to girls (my physical appearance is in normal standards), but I have been able to date and get companionship with no much effort. I dont like to have too many possessions and I prefer to be alone or with a small group of friends (I make it and lost it so easily). I don't have any illness and my mental stability is tremendously tenacious. (I have supported and advise many lives, in certain way I can say I literally have saved lives; so many of them admire my "wisdom")
It can be said that I don't have any problem; however, there is something, something inside my that is revolting since very early times in my life: I am not able to stop questioning everything. After, I think, my 22 yo, those questions, with a more mature context and with a broader vision of life have become more intense/fundamental, after 26 yo and especially now I am dealing with the existence of my-self and all other things. I feel loosing my-self in which other may assure "trivial", I think the more the time pass by, the more senseless my life becomes, I lost my drive (and my willingness now is conditioned to temporary contexts), it is like the meaning of all the things I have done for me and others is vague. Why am I doing all the good and the bad? Why am I believing that I need to find a real "meaning of life"? 
I don't have problems with enjoying life, I feel all the range the emotions, the good and bad emotions, I have suffered as many of us the violence of this world, the love of this one also; however If I stop for a moment and meditate about it, sometimes the outcomes is the doubt instead of desired peace; and this doubt feeds  my permanent vacillation (the dichotomy: all matters, nothing matters) and the result, progressively push me towards something I do not know what it is, but somehow I fear and it seems to be that my life is objectively meaningless.

I have these beautiful recurring dreams of a place I miss from my old home. We used to scramble far and wild across the neighborhood, hoping fences, going to areas restricted to access. But there's a place I recall, that I go to in my dreams, but didn't actually exist in the places I once physically visited when I was still young. In the dream, there are giant plants called elephant ears sprouting, and a massive chasm in the ground, and forests everywhere. From the chasm is such a gale, it sweeps you off your feet if you're not cautious and you can tumble down into this mammoth pit. The gusts are so strong on some days due to the weather, you can get on one of the wide elephant ear leaves and ride it across. It's terrifying, if the wind stalls you'll drop, but usually the gust continues without too dire of interruption and you can skitter across this sprawling pit. I love this dream, it's exhilarating, and there's so much nostalgia for this place that only exists in my dreams. When I'm dreaming of it, though, then it feels like it always was a genuine place that actually existed, that I could find somewhere out there if I searched long enough. Despite it being a frightening realm to visit when I slumber, i feel like times are still simple, and the once ways were never set asunder. Checkpoint: 8-6-2020
The idea of self-worth was always odd to me. I never quite grasped it in regards to myself. I'm living, I have friends, my family loves me,, I'm clearly worth something to someone. But this morning it doesn't feel like that is quite enough. I had depression years ago, and managed to get myself back on my feet. I feel like I'm slipping back into it. 

Passing, joking, comments about how I live off public programs since graduating college, dig deeper than intended, I waste my talent and ideas on playing games. As a high-risk individual I'm imprisoned in my own home during the pandemic. The desire to create something lasting with my life and my youth is finally there, but I cannot go out and pursue it safely. My self-worth is eroding. Being a good friend and a good son isn't sustaining me anymore. I want to contribute my life experiences to the world, but I feel unable to do so right now. It is suffocating.

I keep telling myself ill start pushing as hard as I can to escape this feeling, but I wake up and the weight is almost too much to bear. I believe I will be okay eventually; I just need to get up again. I have to get up again. Everyone is supporting me, I have to keep going for them.

Moving during a pandemic was less stressful than it would seem. I've been extremely homesick the last few weeks, but I've been finding ways around it. I really do like my new place.

Things are pretty bad right now, but I'm glad it hit when it did for me. The end of last year was the first time when I really felt mentally and physically comfortable and even proud of who I am and was in the past, flaws and all. So if the world really wanted to knock my mental state down a few pegs, I'm glad it was during a time where I could handle it in a healthy way rather than say, late 2018 lol. I've never played DKC2, but I played DKC3 Dixie's Double Trouble for the GBA.
It was my first game, which I got alongside my first console, a Silver GBA, all from my Cousin.

I got a far as the bosses of Cottontop Cove and the Factory World. I didn't understand all the mechanics me playing betwee. 6-8 years old, and never got past them.

My Parents had a breakup when i was around 8 and I was wisked to another state, and me not knowing why i was leaving, couldnt find my GBA (I later learned since my father was being unfaithful, the kids of the other person he had over had stolen my GBA and Charger.)

my dog of 6 years was killed by a car July 15th 2018 he was my precious and sacred boy. had plenty of family dogs growing up, but Tommy was MY buddy MY dog. my first like that.  in 2015 had to move raised Tommy before i went to Canada. i'm telling this backwards because right now, in 2020, 2 years after my sweet Tommy Boy left, 2 years after my heart closed so tight from such a great loss, a puppy literally appeared outside of my bedroom window over night. i never thought i would be open to another dog again. i didn't even want another dog. and when Tommy died, i blamed myself for being gone and not somehow taking him with me to Canada. blamed myself for not spending more time with him, or keeping him safer. blaming myself for not being able to keep him off the road that night. blamed myself for so much. on top of the failures in my career path. i was in my 20's during those college times. always scared and stressed. having 1-4 anxiety attacks a day. i even had a particular bathroom and toilet stall i would have them in at school. everyday i thought of Tommy and what he was doing. how his days were. id spend as much time with him as i could on visit home, but i only had 3 visits over 4ish years. i did what i could. but i still wished i did more. still wished i had superpowers and could save him from the car. and now i'm here in my 30's with a life i didn't want, with a life that doesn't have all the shit i worked so fucking hard to achieve, a life with my family i wanted so badly to be free from. a life that i have. a life that somehow, despite everything, makes me so fucking happy. a life that gave me another dog when i least expected it. a life that helped me open my heart back up again. a life that taught me how important it is to mourn and grieve and feel whatever you're feeling as fully as you possibly can feel it. a life that i love. and even though it hasn't turned out at ALL what i had worked for and wanted initially, i still have it. i never get author: Pixx
text:
Relax, and set aside a moment to clear your thoughts. No matter what point in time you're reading this, things are probably hectic. They always seem to be. So it's important every now and then to take the time to ground yourself.
Separate yourself from what's going on around you, and just be comfortable in your own presence. As important as our connections to other people are, you are a complete and whole person by yourself. You are worthy of love, so give it to yourself. You've been through a lot, and you've still got more to overcome, so be nice to yourself.
Ask yourself this: if another person treated you the way you treat yourself, how would you feel about that? Would you treat someone else the way you treat yourself? You may think you know what's best for yourself, but our minds can be deceitful. Often, we lie to ourselves, convincing ourselves that we deserve to hurt. You may not feel worthy of love, or respect, or happiness, but you are. It's okay to admit that.
I've gone on for too long already, so I'll wrap things up. My main message for today is this: recognize your importance. Of course, not in a cocky way, but in a way where you value yourself as you value the people closest to you. You are an important person in the lives of multiple people. It may not always feel that way, but it's true. You can do so much good in this world. I know you can.
Perhaps this comment is a little all over the place, but isn't life? Thank you for reading this long, unnecessarily deep comment. Until we meet again.

As for other things, online classes are a total bore and pose no challenge whatsoever. I‚Äôll slouch down and play video games while everyone else babbles away at stuff. Life‚Äôs currently pretty slow considering the pandemic, winter break, and all that stuff. I don‚Äôt really have much going for me right now. If I had to describe the entire essence of what I‚Äôve been doing for the past few months, it would just be... well, waiting. I‚Äôm just waiting. Waiting for something, anything, to happen. Waiting until I grow up and have the ability to do whatever I want to do, no parents or siblings to hold me down. But then I have the fear of being alone and dying alone with no one to comfort me. I don‚Äôt have any friends to meet up with. Not online and not in person. I‚Äôll occasionally come to family meetings and sit down in a corner somewhere and wait some more till I go back home. I don‚Äôt have any desire to off myself since I still have a few people who care about whether or not I exist. I‚Äôm lazy and overweight, weathering away with each passing second. author: Vincent Wilson
text: Today has been a mixed bag of emotions. I just came back to work after Christmas break yesterday, and everything feels so different. I like my job, it's easy and pays well with benefits, but I can't stand some of the people I work with. They tend to be hypocritical, complaining about something I did or didn't do, and then they go off and do the same thing. It's pretty much the only thing I find frustrating about my job. But while I hate that it happens, I still undecided that under that side I've seen, is a human being, just like me, with their own sets of ideals and truths. I always try to remind myself that I don't know what's going on in their lives to make them act the way they do towards me. While I may get mad at them for the time being, I never hold on to that anger. I let it go, and go on about my day. And every night I catch myself thinking about them, I always end up hoping the best for them, and whatever problems their facing in life become resolved, because we all deserve to be happy in life

author: Reaper.
text: It's the enchanted woods; enchanted means spellbound, possessed, cursed. It's not supposed to be suspenseful or scary--it's enchanted, not haunted. It's supposed to be hypnotic, mesmerizing, or otherwise put you in a trance. In this case, David Wise chose to pick something melodic as the base and in elements that created mystique and mystery while at the same time giving an uncanny calming feeling. It's bewitching, and it's intentional. It's not irony, it's entirely intentional.
